President Trump welcomes Prime Minister Netanyahu to the White House and expresses condolences for the recent Hamas rocket attack on Israeli homes. Trump signs a presidential proclamation recognizing Israel's sovereign right over the Golan Heights, citing the need for Israel to defend itself against security threats from Iran and terrorist groups in southern Syria. The two leaders discuss mutual priorities in the Middle East and beyond, including defense and trade. Netanyahu thanks Trump for his support of Israel and his decisions to withdraw from the Iran nuclear deal, restore sanctions, and recognize Jerusalem as Israel's capital. He calls Trump's recognition of Israel's sovereignty over the Golan Heights a historic act of justice and emphasizes the importance of the Golan Heights for Israel's security. Trump and Netanyahu briefly address questions about the Israeli-Palestinian conflict and other topics before the meeting concludes.